[gd_resource type="Resource" script_class="HandbookPage" load_steps=2 format=3]

[ext_resource type="Script" path="res://resources/HandbookPage.gd" id="1_page"]

[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_page")
page_id = "terminal"
title = "TERMINAL COMMAND REFERENCE"
content = "[b][color=#006CFF]ACTIVE DEFENSE MODULES[/color][/b]
The Terminal provides direct system-level access to all network nodes.

[b]COMMANDS:[/b]
• [b]help[/b]: Display this manual in the terminal.
• [b]list[/b]: List all reachable hostnames on the local network.
• [b]scan [hostname][/b]: Run a diagnostic to find hidden malware processes.
• [b]netstat [hostname][/b]: View active outbound connections. Used to find C2 (Command & Control) servers.
• [b]trace [ip][/b]: Follow the 'digital trail' of an IP to identify its origin.
• [b]isolate [hostname][/b]: Digitally sever a computer from the network.
• [b]restore [hostname][/b]: Reconnect an isolated computer after cleanup.

[b][color=#C62828]PRO TIP:[/color][/b] If you find a suspicious IP in an email, use [b]trace[/b] to see if it belongs to one of our internal servers."
